      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T22:05:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this feels a bit heavy to achieve the goal, but it makes sense to just reuse the existing parser state struct! I don\u0027t have a better suggestion though. If you wanted to avoid extra management, you could calloc(num_syscalls, sizeof(struct parser_state)) then use state.file !\u003d NULL to determine if a syscall was pre-allocated.  But *shrug*.\n\nDo you think there will ever be a need to emit which file assigned which syscall? If so, the other option would be to just keep a syscall_nr bit vector and on first definition emit syscall-defined-here and on subsequent emit syscall-redefined-here.  But we wouldn\u0027t want to have that noise on by default!",
